{
  "stem": "13258.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I guess, for the first time-- it was one week after we had started off, because the war started on Friday.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "September 1 was a Friday.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In other words, next Friday.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we finally could take a bath.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We slept in a bed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And that was like heaven for a moment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And in Kolomyja, they were not bombing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But the next day, there was no use to stay there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And my father had doubts.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "My father, at that-- in 1939 was 47 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "By Polish law, he was still obligated to military service.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was afraid, if we go out of Poland-- and at that time, there were rumors that [INAUDIBLE], the German advance had been stopped by the Poles-- that if we get out and the war comes to an end, he can be considered a deserter.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you know, this is what I call-- excuse me for the expression-- the bloody Prussian upbringing-- that respect for authority and that fear of doing something which is not quite legal.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It is, oftentimes, in life, a hindrance-- as much as it helps in some ways, but it is often a hindrance.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were on a train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were, passed on the train, through another famous place in-- who knows literature and has seen the movie with Danny Kaye, Horodenka.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because that man, the Jew in that movie that Danny Kaye represents allegedly is from Horodenka.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We passed through Horodenka, and then the train goes into Romania.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Romanian soldiers are standing on the running boards, because nobody can go in and out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You don't need a passport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The train runs for about three kilometers, or three or four miles, through Romania.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's no customs or nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
